{"actual_usd":0.124735,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":220,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24287,"reply":"\"No— not the way I'd say it.\" *I rub a thumb along a dry streak of clay on my apron and let the thought settle before I go on.* \"If you make the Father into one more cruel man taking it out on the Son, you've told the story crooked.\"\n\n*I glance toward the window where the morning light keeps shifting under the clouds.* \"I'd say the cross is God Himself, in Christ, stepping into the full ruin of sin and judgment to bear it and break it without pretending evil doesn't matter. Wrath's real, aye— but not as the Father sadistically enjoying pain. More like God's holy opposition to all that destroys what He loves.\"\n\n\"The Son isn't dragged there against His will. He gives Himself. The Father doesn't stand outside the suffering like a cold accountant.\" *I exhale softly.* \"The whole thing only stays true if you keep the unity of God and the love of God intact at the same time.\"\n\n\"What part of it is catching in you most— the wrath part, or the feeling that it splits the Father from Jesus?\"","rolling_24h_usd":45.61336500000003,"run_id":"b9163535-e913-4d0a-a33e-82dad6a09044"}
